body:
### Describe the bug

Specifying the `@TestProfile` on the top level test class does not work if `@Nested` classes are used. For example, the following simple test:

```
@QuarkusTest
@TestProfile(FixedTenantTestProfile.class)
class FixedTenantResolverTest {

    @Inject
    Instance<TenantResolver> tenantResolver;

    @Nested
    class Resolve {

        @Test
        public void happyPath() {
            Optional<String> result = tenantResolver.get().resolve(null, null);

            assertThat(result).contains(FixedTenantTestProfile.TENANT_ID);
        }

    }

}
```

will fail due to the instance not being injected. Furthermore, the specified test profile in the top-level class is ignored.

The `@Nested` classes work fine if no `@TestProfile` is used.

### Expected behavior

* Test profile is respected in all `@Nested` classes if top-level class is annotated. 
* Beans are correctly injected

